Step 1

Firstly, it should be downloaded the nodejs on a machine has internet connection.
It can be download on this link: https://nodejs.org/en/download

Step 2

tar -xvf <your_tar>
//example --> sudo tar -xvf node-v14.15.5-linux-x64.tar.xz


Step 3

Then cp the extracted tar to /usr/ folder
 sudo cp -r directory_name/{bin,include,lib,share} /usr/
//example ---> sudo cp -r node-v14.15.5-linux-x64/{bin,include,lib,share} /usr/

Step 4

Update the path

export PATH=/usr/node_directory_name/bin:$PATH
//example -->export PATH=/usr/node-v14.15.5-linux-x64/bin:$PATH



Step 5

Check the node and npm version

node --version
npm --version















